  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [x] Foundry\r\n- [x] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (a1f41be 2023-03-14T00:15:36.156534Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\n`forge script`\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nSince 93aa2d071b635a838030aa29ad85b52d361f5728 any env variable used in [etherscan] must be present or forge will fail. For instance with:\r\n\r\n```toml\r\n[etherscan]\r\nmumbai={key=\"${POLYGON_API_KEY}\"}\r\n```\r\n\r\nif you run `forge script` locally without verification (and without broadcast) you will get:\r\n\r\n```\r\nFailed to resolve env var `POLYGON_API_KEY` in `${POLYGON_API_KEY}`: environment variable not found\r\n```\r\n\r\nThat was not the case before 93aa2d071b635a838030aa29ad85b52d361f5728. And it makes sense to lazy-load, you can have scripts in a project that will only be run on a local node (and some people will only use it this way). Those will not use some sections of the config file.",
