    "body": "This is already the case: environment variables are only resolved when `Config::get_etherscan...` is called, so on-demand.\r\nI could only reproduce this with a fork url, and the error happens here, when trying to decode Etherscan traces:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/1e0b628d47a7fc18f4fbe0b0b84581fe6a9ad3b3/cli/src/cmd/forge/script/mod.rs#L202-L212\r\n\r\nPreviously the variable wasn't even getting resolved in the first place, so that's why this error never showed up.",
